{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In another work, Li and Womer [40] investigated the assignment-type MS-RCPSP and proposed a HBD algorithm that combines the advantages of MILP and constraint programming.",
    "They also introduced a cut-generating scheme based on temporal analysis in project scheduling to resolve resource conflicts.",
    "In the context of exact solution algorithms, Montoya et al. [41] proposed a branch and price procedure that combined a column generation technique and an activity and time-oriented decomposition scheme, resulting in the discovery of new optimal solutions for previously unknown cases.",
    "Bellenguez-Morineau and Néron [42] also presented two exact methods for solving the RCPSP with alternative resource requirements using the branch and bound algorithm.",
    "These methods employed a search tree to build partial schedules, either by scheduling one activity per node and adding nodes based on eligible activities' possible execution mode or by scheduling the activity at the earliest feasible start time."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In another work, Li and Womer [40] investigated the assignment-type MS-RCPSP and proposed a HBD algorithm that combines the advantages of MILP and constraint programming.",
    "In the context of exact solution algorithms, Montoya et al. [41] proposed a branch and price procedure that combined a column generation technique and an activity and time-oriented decomposition scheme, resulting in the discovery of new optimal solutions for previously unknown cases.",
    "Bellenguez-Morineau and Néron [42] also presented two exact methods for solving the RCPSP with alternative resource requirements using the branch and bound algorithm."
